://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/hudsonvalleyhost-300x191.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/hudsonvalleyhost.png.webp 320w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a>Ernie, from <a href=\"http://hudsonvalleyhost.com/\">Hudson Valley Host</a>, has sent in the following offers for LowEndBox readers. All of these come with DDoS protection by RioRey and are only available in Buffalo, NY, USA.</p><table><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><strong>512MB<br>\n</strong><p></p><ul><li>512MB RAM</li><li>50GB HDD space</li><li>1TB Bandwidth</li><li>100Mbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li><li>Coupon: <span class=\"original\"><strong>60offddosprotvps</strong></span></li><li>$4.80/month</li><li><a href=\"https://billing.hudsonvalleyhost.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=516\">Order here</a></li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>1GB KVM</strong><p></p><ul><li>1GB RAM</li><li>30GB HDD space</li><li>4TB Bandwidth</li><li>100Mbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>KVM/SolusVM</li><li>$7/month</li><li><a href=\"https://billing.hudsonvalleyhost.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=537\">Order here</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>More offers inside!</em></p><p>Hudson Valley Host has been around for a while and has been purchased by ColoCrossing a while ago. ColoCrossing and Hudson Valley Host are both part of VSNX, the organization that owns LowEndBox and LowEndTalk. The DDoS protection is said to protect against \u201c<span class=\"original\">UDP flood, TCP flood, SYN flood, ICMP flood, DNS reflection flood and all layers 1 through 7</span>\u201d according to Ernie and the protection device is located locally in the DC rather than the protection being backhauled through another DC. Attacks up to 10Gbps are handled by this device. Should you give HVH a try as a result of this offer or are you already a customer? We\u2019re looking forward to hear your opinion!</p><p><span id=\"more-6903\"></span></p><table><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><strong>256MB<br>\n</strong><p></p><ul><li>256MB RAM</li><li>25GB HDD space</li><li>500GB Bandwidth</li><li>100Mbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li><li>Coupon: <span class=\"original\"><strong>60offddosprotvps</strong></span></li><li>$4.20/month</li><li><a href=\"https://billing.hudsonvalleyhost.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=515\">Order here</a></li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>1GB</strong><p></p><ul><li>1GB RAM</li><li>100GB HDD space</li><li>2TB Bandwidth</li><li>100Mbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li><li>Coupon: <span class=\"original\"><strong>60offddosprotvps</strong></span></li><li>$5.60/month</li><li><a href=\"https://billing.hudsonvalleyhost.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=517\">Order here</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Hudson Valley Host accepts payments via credit cards and PayPal. They offer a 99.9% uptime guarantee but don\u2019t seem to offer refunds. Servers will be setup instantly once your payment has been made, given that you won\u2019t trigger any fraud protection measures. As usual, we suggest you read their <a href=\"http://www.hudsonvalleyhost.com/tos.php\">Terms of Service</a> before purchasing.</p><p><strong>Network information</strong></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">ColoCrossing \u2013 Buffalo, New York, USA</span><br>\nLooking glass: <a href=\"http://lg-buff.hudsonvalleyhost.com/\">http://lg-buff.hudsonvalleyhost.com/</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fhudson-valley-host-ddos-prote